      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Hans Zellner</b>\n</p><p><b>Hans Zellner</b>,<br />\na German programmer involved in the early development and compression of <a href=\"/Endgame_Tablebases\" title=\"Endgame Tablebases\">endgame tablebases</a>, making three, four and even five piece <a href=\"/Endgame\" title=\"Endgame\">endgames</a> such as <a href=\"/KRK\" title=\"KRK\">KRK</a> (July 1985), KQK (September 1985), <a href=\"/KPK\" title=\"KPK\">KPK</a> (November 1985), KBBK (July 1986), <a href=\"/KBNK_Endgame\" title=\"KBNK Endgame\">KBNK</a>, KQKR, and KBBKN available for <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Home_computer\">home-computers</a>, the three piece endgames and KBBK already on a <a href=\"/Commodore_64\" title=\"Commodore 64\">Commodore 64</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>. He developed a program which perfectly played KQKR to run on an <a href=\"/Atari_ST\" title=\"Atari ST\">Atari ST</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>, a five-piece endgame, KBBKN had to be stored on 59 <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Floppy_disk\">floppy disks</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>. \n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hans_Zellner&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Hans Zellner</a> (<b>1986</b>). <i>Compressing Databases Down to Micro Size</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#9_4\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 9, No. 4</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Hans Zellner</a> (<b>1987</b>). <i>KBBK Squeezed into a Micro</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#10_1\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 10, No. 1</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Hans Zellner</a>, <a href=\"/Jaap_van_den_Herik\" title=\"Jaap van den Herik\">Jaap van den Herik</a>, <a href=\"/Bob_Herschberg\" title=\"Bob Herschberg\">Bob Herschberg</a> (<b>1987</b>). <i>Corrections and Substantiations to KBNK</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#10_3\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 10, No. 3</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Hans Zellner</a> (<b>1989</b>). <i>The KPK Database Revisited</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#12_2\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 12, No. 2</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Hans Zellner</a> (<b>1989</b>). <i>KBBKN on a Micro</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#12_3\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 12, No. 3</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hans_Zellner&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Jaap_van_den_Herik\" title=\"Jaap van den Herik\">Jaap van den Herik</a>, <a href=\"/Bob_Herschberg\" title=\"Bob Herschberg\">Bob Herschberg</a> (<b>1986</b>). <i>A note on KBBK</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#9_4\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 9, No. 4</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Hans Zellner</a> (<b>1986</b>). <i>Compressing Databases Down to Micro Size</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#9_4\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 9, No. 4</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.schachfeld.de/threads/7862-computerschach-und-datenbanken-historischer-sammelthread\">Computerschach und Datenbanken - historischer Sammelthread</a> by hoppelstoppler, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.schachfeld.de/forum.php\">Schachfeld.de</a>, October 18, 2008 (German)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Solutions to our 2012 Christmas Puzzles – Part 2 by <a href=\"/John_Nunn\" title=\"John Nunn\">John Nunn</a>, <a href=\"/ChessBase\" title=\"ChessBase\">ChessBase</a> Christmas Puzzles</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#RefDB\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICGA Reference Database</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260228170244\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.009 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.009 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 81/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 190/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n